defmodule <%= @base_string %>.Auth do
  @moduledoc """
  Authentication primitives: opaque session tokens, password hashing, the
  session sweeper Oban worker, and Swoosh email assembly + delivery.

  This module is intentionally thin — it holds no business logic. Real
  identity work lives in `<%= @base_string %>.Accounts`; tenancy work in
  `<%= @base_string %>.Organizations`. Two cookies carry auth state in this
  app:

    * **Auth session cookie** — opaque random 32-byte token managed directly
      via `Plug.Conn.put_resp_cookie/4`. Hashed (SHA-256) at rest in the
      `sessions` table. HttpOnly, Secure in prod, SameSite=Lax.
    * **`Plug.Session` cookie** — used *only* as the CSRF token carrier. No
      application data lives in its payload. The SPA reads the token from
      `<meta name="csrf-token">` and sends it as `X-CSRF-Token` on every
      mutating XHR.
  """
end
